                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1037">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/5–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-06T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 6, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 6—8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2425. ReEmbtel 2381, May 5, 1 p.m.<note n="90" xml:id="d1037fn90">
                        <ref target="frus1945v04#pg_686">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            686</ref>.</note> Duff Cooper tells me that de Gaulle promised him last
                    night to turn over one brigade of the <hi rend="italic">Troupes Spéciales</hi>
                    to the Syrians in the very near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
